"correlation for 1d arrays. The correlation is computed at each output point "
"by multiplying *op1* by a shifted version of *op2* and summing the result. "
"As a result of the shift, needed values outside of the defined range of "
"*op1* and *op2* are interpreted as zero. The mode determines how many shifts "
"to return: 0 - return only shifts that did not need to assume zero- values; "
"1 - return an object that is the same size as *op1*, 2 - return all possible "
"shifts (any overlap at all is accepted)."
